content:
Verse 1:
In a world of chaos and confusion,
Where war and peace collide,
Golfers take to the green with swords and armor,
And swing their clubs with precision and might.

Chorus:
Golf in the year 3020,
It's a game of survival,
Where the strongest will be the last one standing,
In this strange and twisted world.

Verse 2:
With magic and technology at their fingertips,
These golfers fight for dominance,
They'll stop at nothing to win,
In this game of golf, only the strongest survive.

Chorus:
Golf in the year 3020,
It's a game of survival,
Where the strongest will be the last one standing,
In this strange and twisted world.

Bridge:
So grab your clubs and gear up,
It's time to take to the course,
For in this game of golf,
Only the strongest will emerge victorious.

Gospel Choir:
Golf in the year 3020,
A game of strength and power,
Where the strongest will rise,
And the weak will cower.

Chorus:
Golf in the year 3020,
It's a game of survival,
Where the strongest will be the last one standing,
In this strange and twisted world.
